## Example 1: Signpost — Foreman's Gate

**Slot ID:** img-dock7-gate

**Section Anchor:** s41-dock-inspection

**Purpose:** signpost (checkpoint context; reduce reader hesitation about badge gate)

**Subject:** Foreman's shadow across Dock 7 checkpoint

**Composition Intent:** Low angle, scanner glow; lapel area readable; foreman looms above frame; viewer (player) looking up from below (submissive angle creates tension)

**Iconography:** Badge scanner eye (red glow), union badge silhouette, wet steel, corroded checkpoint frame

**Light/Mood:** Sodium lamps (yellow-orange), wet reflections, industrial tension, slight menace

**Caption:** "Sodium lamps smear along wet steel; the scanner's eye waits."

**Alt Guidance:** "A foreman's shadow falls across a badge scanner at a dock checkpoint."

**Crop/Variant Notes:** 16:9 for screen (landscape suits low angle); 3:2 for print; ensure scanner readable at both scales; consider portrait variant for mobile (tighter on scanner + shadow)

**Inclusion Criteria:** Show when section mentions inspection or badge checks; hide if player has already passed gate

**Determinism Requirement (off-surface):** "Record seed/model or capture settings in determinism log"

**Spoiler Risk:** low (no twist reveals; establishes checkpoint mood and context only)

**Status:** planned

---

## Example 2: Clarify — Salvage Permit Visual

**Slot ID:** img-salvage-permit

**Section Anchor:** s23-salvage-claim

**Purpose:** clarify (what a salvage permit looks like; aids comprehension of bureaucratic process)

**Subject:** Stamped document with station seal

**Composition Intent:** Close-up; stamp and signature visible; weathered paper texture; desk surface beneath (bureaucratic context)

**Iconography:** Station seal (geometric station logo), official stamps (red ink, crisp edges), handwritten authorization, document creases (worn but official)

**Light/Mood:** Desk lamp (warm, focused), bureaucratic formality, slightly worn (this permit has history)

**Caption:** "The clerk stamps your salvage permit—ink dark, seal crisp."

**Alt Guidance:** "A stamped document with a station seal authorizing salvage rights."

**Crop/Variant Notes:** Square crop for mobile (stamp centered); landscape for print (more document context); keep stamp always centered and readable

**Inclusion Criteria:** First mention of salvage permit in player's path; can reuse in inventory view if needed

**Determinism Requirement (off-surface):** "Log generation parameters if synthetic; capture settings if photo-based; maintain consistent seal design across all instances"

**Spoiler Risk:** low (purely administrative; no plot reveals)

**Status:** planned

---

## Example 3: Mood — Station Vista at Night

**Slot ID:** img-station-night

**Section Anchor:** s12-arrival

**Purpose:** mood (establish industrial atmosphere and scale; player's first view of station)

**Subject:** Exterior station view, distant lights, curved hull

**Composition Intent:** Wide shot, depth through light layers, player POV from small ship approaching; scale comparison (small ship vs massive station); curvature suggests size

**Iconography:** Running lights (red/green navigation standard), antenna arrays, docking clamps, habitation ring lights (warm windows), cargo bay lights (cold industrial)

**Light/Mood:** Deep space black, scattered station lights (warm habitation vs cold industrial), isolation with purpose, anticipation

**Caption:** "A thousand lights stud the dark—home for fifty thousand, dock for you."

**Alt Guidance:** "A large space station curves against darkness, lights marking docking bays and habitation rings."

**Crop/Variant Notes:** Ultra-wide 21:9 for immersion (desktop/web); 16:9 fallback with tighter crop on station curve; avoid square crop (loses scale)

**Inclusion Criteria:** Chapter opening; sets emotional baseline for act; first view of station

**Determinism Requirement (off-surface):** "Full render log: seed, model version, composition layers (lights, hull, space), aspect, post-process (glow, color grading)"

**Spoiler Risk:** low (establishes setting only; no narrative reveals)

**Status:** rendering (assigned to Illustrator)

---

## Example 4: Recall — Union Badge Close-up

**Slot ID:** img-union-badge

**Section Anchor:** s35-badge-reveal

**Purpose:** recall (player saw this in gate scene; now it becomes plot-relevant; badge details matter for later recognition)

**Subject:** Union badge detail, worn edges, member number

**Composition Intent:** Macro shot; badge fills frame; wear patterns tell story of use (scratches, fading); viewer sees badge as owner would (intimate personal item)

**Iconography:** Union symbol (crossed tools—wrench and spanner), member ID (generic number visible but not legible enough to read specific digits), authentication strip (holographic or colored), lanyard clip (worn metal)

**Light/Mood:** Warm personal light (contrast to cold scanner light from gate scene; this is "yours"); badge as identity, not just access token

**Caption:** "Your union badge—edges worn smooth, number still bright."

**Alt Guidance:** "A close-up of a worn union badge showing a member ID number and authentication strip."

**Crop/Variant Notes:** Square or portrait; ensure ID number readable but not legible (avoid spoiling specific number unless narratively relevant); focus on worn edges (tells story of long use)

**Inclusion Criteria:** When player examines badge in inventory or reflects on union membership; use as recall anchor when badge becomes plot point

**Determinism Requirement (off-surface):** "Consistent badge design across all appearances (gate scene, inventory, plot reveal); log badge template parameters; maintain wear pattern consistency"

**Spoiler Risk:** medium (badge details may hint at union role or standing; keep number generic; avoid revealing rank or faction)

**Status:** planned

